Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
detachModulePort(25.10)                                detachModulePort(25.10)

Name
       detachModulePort  - Detaches the net connected to the specified port on
       the specified hierarchical instance

Syntax
       detachModulePort

       [-help]

       <hinstName>

       <portName>

       Detaches the net connected to the specified port on the specified hier-
       archical instance.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each detachModulePort.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man detachModulePort

       <hinstName>
              Specifies the name of the hierarchical instance.

              To  detach a top-level port, specify "-" as the <hinstName>. For
              example, the following command detaches the port  'a'  from  the
              net connected to it:

              >detachModulePort - a

       <portName>
              Specifies the port on the module.

Example
              * The following command detaches port p1 from moduleA:

                detachModulePort moduleA p1

Related Information
              * attachModulePort

              * deleteModulePort

